<a class="bookmark" title="Bed Bugs and Schools and Daycares" name="schools"></a>
<h2>Bed Bugs and Schools and Daycares</h2>
<p>Bed bugs prefer an environment where they can hide during the day and come out at night to feed. Most schools or daycare settings do not offer this type of environment; however, bed bugs can hide in clothing and personal belongings such as backpacks and lunch bags. This provides them an opportunity to migrate and spread to other individuals.</p>
<hr/>
<a class="bookmark" title="Bed Bug Prevention" name="prevention"></a>
<h2>Bed Bug Prevention</h2>
<p>Schools are required to have a school Integrated Pest Management Program (IPM) in place that should address all forms of pests. Trained staff should be available to identify bed bugs in the classroom, on children’s items, and be able to identify bed bug bites on children. Please treat students respectfully and handle the situations discreetly. Information should be sent to students for their families and educational seminars should be held for the benefit of the school community.</p>
